SUMMARY:Building Community Through Culture Gala
LOCATION:701 Channelside Drive Tampa \, FL 33602 United States
DESCRIPTION:Don your best cocktail chic in colors of red\, green\, black a
 ndor gold and attend the BUILDING COMMUNITY THROUGH CULTURE GALA\, the ina
 ugural fundraising event supporting the construction of the Tampa Bay Afri
 can American Arts Culture Center. The elegant evening will highlight the o
 rganizations mission to strengthen the communitys quality of life by creat
 ing a safe\, inclusive space for people of all ages to connect through art
 \, learning and culture. Be a part of history. Purchase your tickets today
 ! During the gala at The Florida Aquarium\, you will enjoy: - Live Music b
 y The Beat Down Band - Silent Auction (concert tickets\, day outings) - Li
 ve Auction (trips\, experiences) - Gala Bid (raise your paddle) - Games Fu
 nds raised during the gala will directly support efforts to: - Elevate Afr
 ican American artists and creatives - Preserve cultural history and artist
 ic expression - Provide arts education and access to youth and families - 
 Strengthen community connection through cultural programming Upon its comp
 letion\, the TAAAC will exist to celebrate\, preserve\, and advance Africa
 n American arts and culture throughout the Tampa Bay community. Through dy
 namic programming and collaborative initiatives\, the organization will cr
 eate space for voices\, stories\, and creativity that have shaped the regi
 ons cultural legacy and continue to inspire future generations. Be a part 
 of history. Purchase your tickets today. \n\nPermalink: https://www.tampa.
 gov/node/191586
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.tampa.gov/node/191586
END:VEVENT
